  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Social Cohesion between Host Communities and Internally Displaced Persons in the Center North Region of Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project contributes to strengthening the social cohesion in Kaya (Center-North region), Burkina Faso, by improving relations between the displaced populations and the host communities. It mobilizes all actors and institutional mechanisms, traditional and official, capable of producing a qualitative change in the perception and in the behavior for an improved acceptance between host and displaced communities. To achieve this, the project seeks to improve acceptance between host and displaced communities by eliminating clich&#xE9;s, prejudices and stigmatizations, which are a source of conflict, mistrust and rejection. Achieving this goal is only possible through the collective participation of all social groups in the improvement of a community infrastructure and the roll-out of awareness-raising actions that will enable communities to get to know each other and work together for the greater good.</narrative>
  </description>
